0.1 Introduction

In this Rmarkdown we are going to plot panels A, B & C. In this script we will use the Visium data coming from spatial_analysis/05-sc_mapping/07-sc_mapping_viz.Rmd.

SpatialColors <- colorRampPalette(colors = rev(x = brewer.pal(n = 11, name = "Spectral")))

0.4 Load data

Load Visium data

# 07-sc_mapping_viz.Rmd
# se_obj <- "{map_27}/{robj_dir}/se_deconv_{sample_id}_epid20_pre-rotation.rds"

sp_ls <- lapply(id_sp_df$gem_id, function(id) {

  se_obj <- "{map_27}/{robj_dir}/se_deconv_{id}_epid20.rds" %>%
    glue::glue() %>%
    here::here() %>%
    readRDS(file = .)

  return(se_obj)
})

se_obj <- merge(sp_ls[[1]], y = sp_ls[2:length(sp_ls)],
                add.cell.ids = id_sp_df$gem_id,
                project = "Gloria-Salva")

0.5 Panels

0.5.1 Panel A

In this panel we will show marker genes related to Glial and Glial progenitor on the Visium slide.

rownames(se_obj)[stringr::str_detect(string = rownames(se_obj), pattern = "S100b")]
## [1] "mm10---S100b"
feats_a <- c("mm10---S100b", "mm10---Scn7a", "mm10---Sox10")

a_ls <- lapply(feats_a, function(feat) {
  
  tmp_row <- lapply(img_order, function(img) {
    
    tmp <- Seurat::SpatialPlot(
      object = se_obj,
      features = feat,
      images = img,
      image.alpha = 0,
      crop = FALSE,
      pt.size.factor = 1.25) &
      ggplot2::scale_fill_gradientn(
        colours = SpatialColors(n = 100),
        limits = c(0, max(se_obj@assays$Spatial@data[feat, ])))
    
  }) %>%
    ggpubr::ggarrange(
      plotlist = .,
      nrow = 1,
      common.legend = TRUE,
      legend = "right")
  })

Join panel A

panel_a <- cowplot::plot_grid(
  plotlist = a_ls,
  align = "hv",
  axis = "trbl",
  nrow = 3)

panel_a

"{fig_pt}/{plt_dir}/Extended_26-A.pdf" %>%
  glue::glue() %>%
  here::here() %>%
  cowplot::save_plot(
    filename = .,
    plot = panel_a,
    base_height = 10,
    base_width = 15)
